    "client_msg_id": "a3067c1d-76ea-4ee9-a9f2-8042fd0c8ad3",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I doubt there is much of a connection. Prolog programs don't have any termination guarantees, so you can't use them to prove any theorems (since a program is supposed to correspond to a proof, but a non-terminating program is a proof with a big hole in it).",
